8. Function Expression

	Function is declared by using the function statement. A declared function is used for later use, when the function call invoked. 
Return statement is used to return the value of that function.
	
	Example:
	FunctionName( Parameters) {
	// Code of Logic;
	}
	
	function sum(int a = 5, int b = 5) {
	return a * b;
	}
